[1
Date: 16 Jun 2001
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source El Pais, 16 Jun 2001, [edited
<http://www.elpais.es/articulo.html?d_date=20010616&xref=20010616elpepueco_1&type=Tes&anchor=elppor>

4 more outbreaks of Classical Swine Fever (CSF) have been detected in
Spain, one of them in Castellon, (Valencia) more than 400 km away from the
first infected farm. Another 3 outbreaks in Lerida (Catalunya) have also
been confirmed by the Ministry of Agriculture, including one in Golmes
about 40 km from the original one in Soses.
